<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{five^grade}} verbs form the @HI{{te}}-form in an irregular manner as shown in the table above.
Note that @HI{{iku}} has an irregular @HI{{te}}-form.
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{ichi^grade}} verbs form the @HI{{te}}-form by dropping the final @HI{{ru}}
and adding the suffix @HI{{te}}.
</p>

<p>
The two irregular verbs conjugate as shown above.
</p>

<p>
Note that the @HI{{te}}-form and the <a href="grammar-verb-formation-ta.html">@HI{{ta}}-form</a> (@Vta{{}})
are formed idenitcally except that
@HI{{te}} in the former becomes @HI{{ta}} in the latter and @HI{{de}} becomes @HI{{da}}.
</p>

